                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d511">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5061</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-09T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 9, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1474. Your 1216, April 24, 3 p.m.,<note n="2" xml:id="d511fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_595">p. 595</ref>.</note> and
                    1321, May 25, 5 p.m.<note n="3" xml:id="d511fn3">Not printed.</note> Shipping
                    Board advise that utmost is being done to secure vessels for Archangel trade;
                    that steamers <hi rend="italic">Nassovia</hi> and <hi rend="italic"
                        >Portonia</hi> already in Archangel service; that board is in daily
                    communication with Russian commercial attaché, who has submitted list of
                    requirements; and that it has been policy of board to dispatch ships as they
                    come from repair yards to France, Italy and Russia, share and share alike.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
